<h1>Higher Order Components</h1>
<p>Ptolemy II includes a number of higher-order components. These are actors that operate
on the structure of the model rather than on input data.</p>

<p>
The MultiInstanceComposite actor may be used to instantiate 
identical processing blocks within a model. See the
<a href="../../../../../doc/codeDoc/ptolemy/actor/lib/hoc/MultiInstanceComposite.html">javadoc MultiInstanceComposite documentation</a> for details.

<p>
<a href="../../../../../doc/design/usingVergil/BuildingGraphicalModels.pdf" target="_top">Building Graphical Models</a> describes how to use higher-order components.</p>

